; Regression test for issue #1165: register report need grouping option of no grouping at all (BZ#1165)
; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/1165
;
; The issue requests an explicit "no grouping" option to override grouping
; set via --group-by or period options (e.g. in a .ledgerrc config file).
; Without such an option, grouping set in a config file cannot be cancelled
; on the command line.
;
; This test documents that the basic register command (without any grouping
; flags) produces flat, ungrouped output (individual transactions in order).
; The requested --no-group-by type option was never added.

2014/01/01 Payee A
    Expenses:Food    $10.00
    Assets:Cash

2014/01/15 Payee B
    Expenses:Food    $20.00
    Assets:Cash

2014/02/05 Payee C
    Expenses:Food    $15.00
    Assets:Cash

test reg
14-Jan-01 Payee A               Expenses:Food                $10.00       $10.00
                                Assets:Cash                 $-10.00            0
14-Jan-15 Payee B               Expenses:Food                $20.00       $20.00
                                Assets:Cash                 $-20.00            0
14-Feb-05 Payee C               Expenses:Food                $15.00       $15.00
                                Assets:Cash                 $-15.00            0
end test

test reg --group-by payee
Payee A
14-Jan-01 Payee A               Expenses:Food                $10.00       $10.00
                                Assets:Cash                 $-10.00            0

Payee B
14-Jan-15 Payee B               Expenses:Food                $20.00       $20.00
                                Assets:Cash                 $-20.00            0

Payee C
14-Feb-05 Payee C               Expenses:Food                $15.00       $15.00
                                Assets:Cash                 $-15.00            0
end test
